  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sierra Leone: Ebola Response in Koinadugu District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Koinadugu district Doctors of the World Spain is actively engaged in a prevention and education campaign to fight the spread of Ebola.  We are additional assisting local health professionals and health centers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Technical support for the District Medical Officer


-Reinforcement of staff in charge of the isolation unit and at primary healthcare centers

-Logistics support for application of national hygienic-preventive protocol

-Mapping of community and religious leaders, traditional healers, civil society representatives, associations and NGOs

-Creation and coordination of Social Mobilization/Health Education Committee

-Training for NGOs&apos; and associations&apos; staff, community and religious leaders, civil society representatives and traditional healers on how to deal with social mobilization and health education 

-Social mobilization and health education campaign in Kabala and in the 6 Chiefdoms of Koinadugu

-Supply of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)

-Set up an Isolation Unit at Kabala Hospital and build of the new Holding Center in Kasumpe.</narrative>
  </description>
